 Israel’ former President and Nobel Peace Prize winner Shimon Peres, the last of the country’s founding fathers, was in critical condition on Wednesday after suffering a major stroke and doctors were treating him in intensive care.Mr. Peres has held nearly every major office in the country, including Prime Minister twice and President, a mostly ceremonial post, from 2007 to 2014. — AFP